findings.title: DoS with block gas limit
findings.description: The contract may be vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) attacks due to the block gas limit.

findings.title: Owner can lock and unlock
findings.description: The owner has privileges to lock and unlock, which could allow them to retake privileges even after ownership was renounced.

findings.title: Owner can include in and exclude from reward
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to include or exclude addresses from rewards, which may lead to unintended consequences.

findings.title: Owner can include in and exclude from the fee
findings.description: The owner has privileges to include or exclude addresses from the fee.

findings.title: Owner can change the tax and liquidity fee
findings.description: The contract owner has the privilege to modify the tax and liquidity fee.

findings.title: Owner can change numTokensSellToAddToLiquidity
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to change numTokensSellToAddToLiquidity.

findings.title: Owner can change the maximum transaction amount
findings.description: The contract owner has the privilege to modify the maximum transaction amount.

findings.title: Owner can enable / disable swap and liquify
findings.description: The owner has privileges to enable or disable swap and liquidity functionality.

findings.title: Owner can change marketing, dev and jackpot address
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to modify marketing, development, and jackpot addresses.

findings.title: Owner can withdraw BNBs from contract
findings.description: The owner has the privilege to withdraw BNBs from the contract.

findings.title: Out of gas exception in includeInReward() function
findings.description: The function includeInReward() uses a loop to find and remove addresses from the _excluded list, which can cause an OUT_OF_GAS exception if there is a long excluded addresses list.

findings.title: Out of gas exception in _getCurrentSupply function
findings.description: The function _getCurrentSupply uses a loop to evaluate total supply and may be aborted with an OUT_OF_GAS exception if there is a long excluded addresses list.
